div.p: CMS Engine is a service operated through rest or graphql-api. It can have multiple projects, and holds information about page hierarchy per project. A hierarchy has pages, and a page uses a page template.

When user requests compiled page, Engine merges data from page and pageTemplate to return valid html in json-response. Engine can also be used to return chunks of html, if only certain area of a webpage is wanted to be controlled over CMS.
In pageTemplate there is marked content slots, and in page there's corresponding content entities.
